{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"gre-random","unitId":"word-list-15","title":"Word List 15","sectionId":"gre-core","sectionTitle":"核心词汇","pageStart":183,"pageEnd":193,"extractionMethod":"ocr","wordEntryCount":122,"duplicateEntryCount":35,"pages":[{"number":183,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List15"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缀预习表"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓含义"},{"type":"text","text":"例词及释义"},{"type":"text","text":"词根/词缓含义"},{"type":"text","text":"例词及释义"},{"type":"entry","text":"ultim","headword":"ultim"},{"type":"text","text":"最后"},{"type":"text","text":"ultimate acj. 最后的"},{"type":"text","text":"计数"},{"type":"text","text":"numerous adj.许多的"},{"type":"text","text":"numer"},{"type":"entry","text":"auto","headword":"auto"},{"type":"text","text":"自己"},{"type":"text","text":"autobiography n.自传"},{"type":"text","text":"nutri"},{"type":"text","text":"滋养"},{"type":"text","text":"nutrient n. 营养品"},{"type":"entry","text":"psycho","headword":"psycho"},{"type":"text","text":"心灵，精神psychological adj 心理学的"},{"type":"text","text":"soci"},{"type":"text","text":"结交"},{"type":"text","text":"sociable adj. 好交际的"},{"type":"entry","text":"limin","headword":"limin"},{"type":"text","text":"门楼"},{"type":"text","text":"preliminary adj. 预备的"},{"type":"text","text":"sol"},{"type":"text","text":"太阳"},{"type":"text","text":"solemn adj. 严肃的;庄严的"},{"type":"entry","text":"foli","headword":"foli"},{"type":"text","text":"树叶"},{"type":"text","text":"foliage n. 子"},{"type":"text","text":"tox"},{"type":"text","text":"毒"},{"type":"text","text":"toxic adj有毒的；中毒的"},{"type":"entry","text":"understate","headword":"understate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.保守地说，轻描淡写地说(to state with less completeness or truth than seems"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andar'stert]"},{"type":"text","text":"warranted by the facts)"},{"type":"text","text":"组合词：under（在-下面）+state（说话）→在下面说→保守地说"},{"type":"text","text":"Because of its inclination to uncerstate, most Indian art is reminiscent of"},{"type":"text","text":"Japanese art, where symbols have been minimized and meaning has been"},{"type":"text","text":"conveyed by the merest suggestion."},{"type":"text","text":"understated（adj轻描淡写的，低调的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"evil","headword":"evil"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.邪恶的，罪恶的(sinful, wicked） n. 坏事，恶行(sth. that brings sorrow, distress,"},{"type":"text","text":"[ivl]"},{"type":"text","text":"or calamity)"},{"type":"text","text":"atrocious, foul, malicious, vile"},{"type":"entry","text":"shifting","headword":"shifting"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.变动的：运动的"},{"type":"text","text":"['§rftn]"},{"type":"text","text":"changing, moving"},{"type":"entry","text":"bumper","headword":"bumper"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.特大的（unusually large)n.保险杠(a device for absorbing shock or"},{"type":"text","text":"['bAmpar]"},{"type":"text","text":"preventing damage)"},{"type":"entry","text":"overconfident","headword":"overconfident"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj过于自信的，自负的"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar'ka:nfrdant]"},{"type":"entry","text":"energize","headword":"energize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.给予精力、能量（to make energetic, vigorous,or active）"},{"type":"text","text":"['enardzaiz]"},{"type":"text","text":"activize, invigorate, reinforce, vitalize"},{"type":"entry","text":"sweep","headword":"sweep"},{"type":"definition","text":"v席卷，扫过(to clean with or as if with a broom or brush)"},{"type":"text","text":"[swi:p]"},{"type":"text","text":"sweep theboard（在比赛中）囊括所有奖项"},{"type":"entry","text":"acquiescence","headword":"acquiescence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.默许(the act of acquiescing)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,aekwi'esns]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自acquiesce（v默认，默许）"},{"type":"entry","text":"repetitious","headword":"repetitious"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 董复的(characterized or marked by repetition)"},{"type":"text","text":"[repa'tifas]"}]},{"number":184,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 15 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"dismal","headword":"dismal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj泪丧的，阴沉的(showing sadness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dizmal]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自拉丁文diesmail，意为“不吉利的日子”，后转变为“沮丧的，阴沉的”"},{"type":"text","text":"的意思"},{"type":"text","text":"留 Despite a string of clismal earnings reports, the two-year-old strategy to return"},{"type":"text","text":"the company to profitability is beginning to work."},{"type":"entry","text":"cordiality","headword":"cordiality"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 诚@,热诚(sincere affection and kindness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ko:rd3i'aelati]"},{"type":"text","text":"heartiness, geniality, warmth"},{"type":"entry","text":"ultimate","headword":"ultimate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adji. 最后的(being or happening at the end of a process or course of action)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Altrmat]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ultim（最后）+ate(的）→最后的"},{"type":"text","text":"This project is the first step in a long-range plan of research whose uiltimate"},{"type":"text","text":"goal, still many years off, is the creation of a new prototype."},{"type":"entry","text":"coherence","headword":"coherence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.条理性，连贯性(the quality or state of cohering)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kau'hirans]"},{"type":"text","text":"adherence, adhesion, bond, cohesion"},{"type":"text","text":"coherent（adj.连贯的，一致的）;incoherent（adj.不连贯的；语无伦次的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"patronizing","headword":"patronizing"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj以恩惠态度对待的，要人领情的"},{"type":"text","text":"['pertranaizin]"},{"type":"text","text":"To take a patronizing attitude, looking down on others as one's inferiors, often"},{"type":"text","text":"is to eliminate any chance of favorable relations with them."},{"type":"entry","text":"incredulity","headword":"incredulity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.怀疑，不相信（disbelief)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rnkra'du:lati]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：in（不）+cred（信任）+ulity→怀疑，不相信"},{"type":"entry","text":"incidental","headword":"incidental"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.作为自然结果的，伴随而来的(being likely to ensue as a chance or minor"},{"type":"text","text":"[nsr'dentl]"},{"type":"text","text":"consequence);偶然发生的(occurring merely by chance )"},{"type":"text","text":"Because we have completed our analysis of the major components of the"},{"type":"text","text":"proposed project, we are free to devote the remainder of this session to a study"},{"type":"text","text":"of the project's inciclental details."},{"type":"text","text":"fragment"},{"type":"entry","text":"fragment","headword":"fragment"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 碎片(small part or piece);片段(an incomplete or"},{"type":"text","text":"[fraegmant]"},{"type":"text","text":"isolated portion)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：frag（打碎）+ment（表名词）→碎片"},{"type":"text","text":"scrap, shred"},{"type":"entry","text":"artistry","headword":"artistry"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 艺术技I巧(skill of an artist)"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:rtrstri]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：artist（艺术家）+ry→艺术技巧"}]},{"number":185,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"debate","headword":"debate"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.正式的辩论，讨论(formal argument of a question)v讨论，辩论"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'bert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：de（加强）+bat（打，击）+e→加强打击→正式的辩论"},{"type":"entry","text":"autobiography","headword":"autobiography"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 自传(story of a person’s life written by that person)"},{"type":"text","text":"[:tabar'a:grafi]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：auto（自己）+bio（生命）+graphy（写）→写自己的一生→自传"},{"type":"entry","text":"generalize","headword":"generalize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 概括, 归纳(to draw a general conclusion from particular examples)"},{"type":"text","text":"['dsenralarz]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：general(概括的）+ize→概括，归纳"},{"type":"entry","text":"overblown","headword":"overblown"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj盛期已过的，残败的（past the prime of bloom）：弯张的(inflated)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar'blaun]"},{"type":"entry","text":"systematic","headword":"systematic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 系统的，体系的(relating to or consisting of a system)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,srsta'maetrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"It has been argued that politics as a practice, whatever its transcendental"},{"type":"text","text":"claims, has always been the systermatic organization of common hatreds."},{"type":"entry","text":"naturalistic","headword":"naturalistic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 自然主义的(of, characterized by, or according with naturalism)"},{"type":"text","text":"[naet{ra'istik]"},{"type":"text","text":"natural, realistic, true, truthful"},{"type":"entry","text":"desirable","headword":"desirable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 值得要的(advisable, worthwhile, beneficial)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'zararabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自desire（v/n.渴望）"},{"type":"entry","text":"excessive","headword":"excessive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 过度的, 过分的(exceeding what is usual, proper, necessary, or normal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rk'sesiv]"},{"type":"text","text":"Unfortunately, excessive care in choosing one’s words often results in a loss"},{"type":"text","text":"of spontaneity."},{"type":"text","text":"exorbitant, extravagant, extreme, immoderate, inordinate"},{"type":"text","text":"excessively（adv.过度地）"},{"type":"entry","text":"psychological","headword":"psychological"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 心理学的(of or relating to psychology);心理的，精神的(directed toward the"},{"type":"text","text":"[sarka/la:d3rkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"will or the mind specifically in its conative function)"},{"type":"text","text":"圈词根记忆：psycho（心灵，精神）+log（说）+ical（的）→心理的，精神的"},{"type":"text","text":"In a nation where the economic reversals of the past few years have"},{"type":"text","text":"taken a psychological as well as a financial toll on many regions, what most"},{"type":"example","text":"distinguishes the South may be the degree of optimism throughout the region."},{"type":"entry","text":"erudition","headword":"erudition"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 博学(extensive knowledge acquired chiefly from books)"},{"type":"text","text":"[erja'drfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"eruditeness, scholarship"},{"type":"entry","text":"impressed","headword":"impressed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj被打动的，被感动的"},{"type":"text","text":"[xm'prest]"},{"type":"text","text":"be impressed by（对--)钦佩，有深刻的好印象"},{"type":"entry","text":"characterize","headword":"characterize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.表现-的特色，刻画的性格（to describe the character or quality of)"},{"type":"text","text":"['kaeraktaraiz]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自character（n.人或事物的特点、特征）"}]},{"number":186,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 15 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"interruption","headword":"interruption"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.中断，打断"},{"type":"text","text":"[xnta'rapjn]"},{"type":"text","text":"break, disruption, pause, suspension"},{"type":"entry","text":"readable","headword":"readable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 易读的(able to be read easily)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ri:dabl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"captivating","headword":"captivating"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 引1人的9(very attractive and interesting. in a way that holds your attention)"},{"type":"text","text":"['kaptrvertin]"},{"type":"text","text":"hatch"},{"type":"entry","text":"hatch","headword":"hatch"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.船舱盖(a covering for a ship’s hatchway) v.孵化(to"},{"type":"text","text":"[hat]"},{"type":"text","text":"produce young by incubation); 策划(to bring into being:"},{"type":"text","text":"originate)"},{"type":"text","text":"图hatch a plot策划阴谋"},{"type":"entry","text":"veracity","headword":"veracity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.真实(devotion to the truth);诚实(truthfulness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[va'raesati]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ver（真实的）+acity→真实"},{"type":"example","text":"Trying to prove Hill a liar, Senator Specter repeatedlly questioned her veracity."},{"type":"entry","text":"topple","headword":"topple"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.倾疆，推倒(to overthrow)"},{"type":"