":"gripping","headword":"gripping"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 吸引注意力的,扣人心弦的(holding the interest strongly)"},{"type":"text","text":"['gripin]"},{"type":"text","text":"Teling griping tales about a central character engaged in a mighty struggle"},{"type":"text","text":"with events, modern biographies satisfy the American appetite for epic"},{"type":"text","text":"narratives."},{"type":"entry","text":"unrecognized","headword":"unrecognized"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad未被承认的，未被认出的"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'rekagnaizd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"reclusive","headword":"reclusive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 隐通的，隐居的(seeking or preferring seclusion or isolation)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'klu:srv]"},{"type":"entry","text":"ordinary","headword":"ordinary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.普通的，平常的（routine，usual)：拙劣的，质量差的(deficient in quality: of"},{"type":"text","text":"['s:rdneri]"},{"type":"text","text":"poor or inferior quality) n. 惯例，寻常情况(the regular or customary condition or"},{"type":"text","text":"course of things)"},{"type":"text","text":"commonplace, quotidian, unremarkable"},{"type":"entry","text":"suspense","headword":"suspense"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 悬念(pleasant excitement as to a decision or outcome):挂念(anxiety)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'spens]"},{"type":"text","text":"apprehension, uncertainty"},{"type":"entry","text":"obese","headword":"obese"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 极胖的(corpulent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[au'bi:s]"},{"type":"text","text":"obesity(n.过度肥胖；肥胖症）"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.遥远：偏僻"},{"type":"entry","text":"remoteness","headword":"remoteness"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'mautnas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"preliminary","headword":"preliminary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 预备的，初步的，开始的(coming before a more important action or event;"},{"type":"text","text":"[prr'lzmrneri]"},{"type":"text","text":"preparatory)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：pre（前）+limin（门楼）+ary→入门前的→预备的"},{"type":"entry","text":"culinary","headword":"culinary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.厨房的(of the kitchen);烹调的(of cooking)"},{"type":"text","text":"['kAlineri]"},{"type":"text","text":"culinary skills烹饪技巧"},{"type":"entry","text":"incomplete","headword":"incomplete"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不完全的，不完整的（not complete）"},{"type":"text","text":"[rnkam'plit]"}]},{"number":188,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 15 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"gravitational","headword":"gravitational"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 万有引力的，重力的(of or relating to gravitational force)"},{"type":"text","text":"[graevr'ter{anl]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自gravitation（n.引力;倾向)"},{"type":"text","text":"Clearly refuting sceptic, researchers have demonstrated not only that"},{"type":"text","text":"gravitationa/ radliation exists but that it also does exactly what theory predicted it"},{"type":"text","text":"should do."},{"type":"entry","text":"eminence","headword":"eminence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.卓越，显赫，杰出（a position of prominence or superiority)"},{"type":"text","text":"['eminans]"},{"type":"text","text":"distinction, illustriousness, preeminence"},{"type":"entry","text":"romance","headword":"romance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.传奇故事：虚构（something that lacks basis in fact)：浪漫氛围；风流韵事(love"},{"type":"text","text":"[raumaens]"},{"type":"text","text":"affair) v 虚格构(to exaggerate or invent detail or incident)"},{"type":"entry","text":"spatial","headword":"spatial"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有关空间的，在空间的(of, relating to, involving. or having the nature of"},{"type":"text","text":"[sperf]"},{"type":"text","text":"space)"},{"type":"entry","text":"idiosyncratic","headword":"idiosyncratic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.特殊物质的，特殊的，异质的（peculiar to the individual)"},{"type":"text","text":"[1diasin'kraetuk]"},{"type":"text","text":"To have true disciples, a thinker must not be too idliosyncratic: any effective"},{"type":"text","text":"intellectual leader depends on the ability of other people to reenact thought"},{"type":"text","text":"processes that did not originate with them."},{"type":"text","text":"characteristic, distinctive"},{"type":"text","text":"idiosyncracy (n.特质)"},{"type":"entry","text":"underestimated","headword":"underestimated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj低估的"},{"type":"text","text":"来自underestimate (v低估)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andar'estrmertrd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"interconnected","headword":"interconnected"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 相互连接的(mutually joined or related)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rntarka'nektid]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：inter（在中间）+connect（连接）+ed→在中间连接→相互连接的"},{"type":"entry","text":"spinning","headword":"spinning"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj旋转的"},{"type":"text","text":"['spinin]"},{"type":"text","text":"revolving, rotating, turning, twirling, wheeling, whirling"},{"type":"entry","text":"grateful","headword":"grateful"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 感激的，感谢的(expressing gratitude; appreciative)"},{"type":"text","text":"['grertfl]"},{"type":"text","text":"园不要和grale（v.磨碎）相混"},{"type":"entry","text":"quantifiable","headword":"quantifiable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.可以计量的：可量化的"},{"type":"text","text":"['kwa:ntifarabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：quant(数量）+ifi+able（可…的）→可以计量的"}]},{"number":189,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"remarkable","headword":"remarkable"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj.值得注意的，显著的(worthy of being or likely to be noticed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rt'ma:rkabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"As delicate and fragile as insect bodies are, it is remarkable that over the"},{"type":"text","text":"ages enough of them have survived, preserved in amber, for scientists to trace"},{"type":"text","text":"insect evolution,"},{"type":"text","text":"extraordinary, singular"},{"type":"entry","text":"carnivorous","headword":"carnivorous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adji. 肉食动物的(flesh-eating)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:r'nivaras]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：carni（看作carn，肉）+vor（吃）+ous→肉食动物的"},{"type":"entry","text":"ignorance","headword":"ignorance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 无知,患肤(lack of knowledge, education, or awareness)"},{"type":"text","text":"['rgnarans]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：ig（不）+（g)nor（知道）+ance→什么都不知道→"},{"type":"text","text":"无知，愚昧"},{"type":"text","text":"麻烦您填个"},{"type":"text","text":"benightedness, illiteracy, unacquaintance"},{"type":"text","text":"调查问卷"},{"type":"text","text":"ignorant（adj无知的，愚昧的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"tedium","headword":"tedium"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.长乏味（boredom)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ti:diam]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：媒体（medium）的节目都很乏味（tedium）"},{"type":"entry","text":"investigate","headword":"investigate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 调查(to examine in order to obtain the truth)"},{"type":"text","text":"[In'vestigert]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：in+vest（背心）+i+gate（大门）→穿上背心出大"},{"type":"text","text":"门去调查→调查"},{"type":"text","text":"investigate"},{"type":"entry","text":"elite","headword":"elite"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 精英;主力，中坚(the group regarded as the best and most powerful)"},{"type":"text","text":"[er'li:t]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：e（向外）+lit（看作lig，选择）+e→选出来的→精英"},{"type":"entry","text":"tentatively","headword":"tentatively"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.试验性地"},{"type":"text","text":"['tentativli]"},{"type":"text","text":"experimentally"},{"type":"entry","text":"elegiac","headword":"elegiac"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 哀欧的，挽欧的(of, relating to, or involving elegy or mourning or expressing"},{"type":"text","text":"[elr'dzarak]"},{"type":"text","text":"sorrow for that which is irrecoverably past) n. 哀,绝(elegy)"},{"type":"entry","text":"fraud","headword":"fraud"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.欺诈，欺骗(deceit, trickery)：骗子(impostor, cheat)"},{"type":"text","text":"现在投资就有"},{"type":"text","text":"100倍回报！"},{"type":"text","text":"[fro:d]"},{"type":"text","text":"Paradoxically. while it is relatively easy to prove"},{"type":"definition","text":"a fraudulent work of art is a fraud, it is often virtually"},{"type":"text","text":"impossible to prove that an authentic one is genuine"},{"type":"entry","text":"vagueness","headword":"vagueness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 含精(unclearness by virtue of being vague)"},{"type":"text","text":"[vergnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"Wincing at the vagueness of the interviewer's wording."},{"type":"text","text":"the scholar was as sensitive to words and phrases as a"},{"type":"text","text":"fraud"},{"type":"text","text":"sectarian is to creeds."},{"type":"entry","text":"irreverent","headword":"irreverent"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj. 不尊敬的(lacking proper respect or seriousness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'revarant]"},{"type":"text","text":"disrespectful"}]},{"number":190,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 15 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"mutable","headword":"mutable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 可变的(capable of change or of being changed); 易变的(capable of or"},{"type":"text","text":"['mju:tabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"liable to mutation)"},{"type":"text","text":"changeable, fluid, mobile, protean"},{"type":"entry","text":"comprehensible","headword":"comprehensible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj可理解的，易于理解的（that can be understood)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:mprr'hensabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：com（全部）+prehens（抓）+ible→全部抓住，掌握住→可理解的"},{"type":"text","text":"incomprehensible（aoj.难以理解的，难懂的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"journalistic","headword":"journalistic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj新闻业的，新闻工作者的(of, relating to,or characteristic of journalism or"},{"type":"text","text":"[,d33:rna’lrstrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"journalists)"},{"type":"text","text":"hazard"},{"type":"entry","text":"hazard","headword":"hazard"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 危险(risk, peril, danger)"},{"type":"text","text":"['hazard]"},{"type":"text","text":"at hazard在危急关头"},{"type":"entry","text":"unmoved","headword":"unmoved"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无动于衷的，冷漠的(not affected by feelings of pity,"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'mu:vd]"},{"type":"text","text":"sympathy)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：un（不）+moved（感动的）→不被感动的→无动"},{"type":"text","text":"于衷的"},{"type":"entry","text":"electromagnetic","headword":"electromagnetic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 电磁的(of, relating to, or produced by electromagnetism)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rlektraumaeg'netik]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：electro（电)+magnetic(磁的）→电磁的"},{"type":"entry","text":"numerous","headword":"numerous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj许多的，很多的"},{"type":"text","text":"['nu:maras]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：numer（计数）+ous→不计其数的→许多的，很多的"},{"type":"text","text":"Known for his commitment to numerous worthy causes, the philanthropist"},{"type":"text","text":"dleserved credit for his altruism."},{"type":"text","text":"abundant, multitudinous, myriad, various"},{"type":"entry","text":"derogatory","headword":"derogatory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不敬的，贬损的(disparaging, belittling)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'ra:gat:ri]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：de（向下）+rog（询问）+at+ory→为贬低某人而询问→贬损的"},{"type":"entry","text":"infrequently","headword":"infrequently"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.稀少地，罕见地"},{"type":"text","text":"[nn'fri:kwantli]"},{"type":"text","text":"rarely, seldom"},{"type":"entry","text":"brute","headword":"brute"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.野兽(beast);残忍的人(a person who is brutal) adj 野兽的：残忍的(brutal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[bru:t]"},{"type":"text","text":"bestial, beastly"},{"type":"entry","text":"generosity","headword":"generosity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 假，大方(willingness to share; unselfishness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dzena'ra:sati]"},{"type":"text","text":"Although ordinarily skeptical about the purity of Robinson’s motives, in this"},{"type":"text","text":"instance Jenkins did not consider Robinson’s generosity to be alloyed with"},{"type":"text","text":"consideration of personal gain."},{"type":"entry","text":"unparalleled","headword":"unparalleled"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无比的, 空前的(having no parallel or equal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'paeraleld]"},{"type":"text","text":"unique, unequaled"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 制降(the manufacture of clayware); 制降工艺(the art or craft of the potter); 陶器"}]},{"number":191,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"improper","headword":"improper"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不合适的，不适当的(incorrect; not regularly or normally formed)"},{"type":"text","text":"indecorous, malapropos, undue, unfitting. unseasonable"},{"type":"text","text":"[rm’pra:par]"},{"type":"entry","text":"competing","headword":"competing"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.有竞争性的（rivalrous)：不相上下的"},{"type":"text","text":"[kam'pitrn]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自compete（v.竞争，对抗）"},{"type":"entry","text":"dissident","headword":"dissident"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 唱反调者(a person who disagrees; dissenter)"},{"type":"text","text":"[disidant]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：dis（分开）+sid（坐）+ent→分开坐的人→唱反调者"},{"type":"entry","text":"neutron","headword":"neutron"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 中子(a particle carrying no electric charge)"},{"type":"text","text":"[nu:tra:n]"},{"type":"entry","text":"assuming","headword":"assuming"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 做慢的，自负的(pretentious, presumptuous)"},{"type":"text","text":"confront"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'su:min]"},{"type":"entry","text":"illicit","headword":"illicit"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 违法的(unlawful, prohibited)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'lrsrt]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：il（不）+licit（合法的）→违法的"},{"type":"entry","text":"solemn","headword":"solemn"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj严肃的：庄严的，隆重的（made with great seriousness)：黑色的"},{"type":"text","text":"['sa:lam]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：sol（太阳）+emn→古代把太阳看作是神圣的→庄严的"},{"type":"entry","text":"flustered","headword":"flustered"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.慌张的，激动不安的（nervous orupset)"},{"type":"text","text":"[flAstard]"},{"type":"text","text":"perturbed, rattled"},{"type":"entry","text":"qualified","headword":"qualified"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 合格的9(having complied with the specific requirements or precedent"},{"type":"text","text":"['kwa:lrfard]"},{"type":"text","text":"conditions);有限制的(limited)"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自动词quality（v具有资格：限制）"},{"type":"text","text":"Even though the general's carefully qualfiedf public statement could hardly be"},{"type":"text","text":"faulted, some people took exception to it."},{"type":"entry","text":"impractical","headword":"impractical"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不切实际的(not wise to put into or keep in practice or effect)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rm'praektrkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"Though one cannot say that Michelangelo was an impractica/ designer, he"},{"type":"text","text":"was, of all nonprofessional architects known, the most adventurous in that he"},{"type":"text","text":"was the least constrained by tradition or precedent."},{"type":"entry","text":"amalgam","headword":"amalgam"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.混合物(a combination or mixture)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'maelgam]"},{"type":"text","text":"国联想记忆：am+alg+am→前后两个am结合→混合物"},{"type":"text","text":"admixture, composite, compound, interfusion"},{"type":"entry","text":"die","headword":"die"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.金属模子，金属印p模(a block of hard metal with a design, etc.cut into it)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dar]"},{"type":"text","text":"园注意不是“死亡”的意思"},{"type":"entry","text":"superficially","headword":"superficially"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.表面上地"},{"type":"text","text":"[,su:par'frfali]"},{"type":"text","text":"shallowly"}]},{"number":192,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 15 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"validate","headword":"validate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使生效(to make legally valid)"},{"type":"text","text":"['vaelidert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：valid（有效）+ate→使生效"},{"type":"entry","text":"insignificant","headword":"insignificant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无价值的，无意义的，无用的(lacking meaning or importance; unimportant)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Insig'nrfrkant]"},{"type":"text","text":"The acts of vandalism that these pranksters had actually perpetrated were"},{"type":"example","text":"insignificant compared with those they had contemplated but had not attempted."},{"type":"text","text":"purposeless, trivial, unmeaning"},{"type":"entry","text":"restore","headword":"restore"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使回复，恢复(to bring sb./sth.back to a former position or condlition);修复，"},{"type":"text","text":"[ri'st>:r]"},{"type":"text","text":"修补(to rebuild or repair sth. so that it is like the original)"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：re（重新）+store（储存）→重新储存→恢复：修复"},{"type":"entry","text":"penetrating","headword":"penetrating"},{"type":"text","text":"adj（声音）响亮的，尖锐的：（气味）刺激的：（思想）敏锐的，有洞察力的（acute，"},{"type":"text","text":"['penitrertin]"},{"type":"text","text":"discerning)"},{"type":"entry","text":"condemnation","headword":"condemnation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 道责(censure, blame)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:ndem'nerfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"conviction, damnation, denunciation"},{"type":"entry","text":"inexpensive","headword":"inexpensive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj廉价的，便宜的(reasonable in price)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Inrk'spensrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"Because many of the minerals found on the ocean floor are still plentiful on"},{"type":"text","text":"land, where mining is relatively inexpensive, mining the ocean flioor has yet to"},{"type":"text","text":"become a profitable enterprise."},{"type":"entry","text":"confidently","headword":"confidently"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.确信地：肯定地（certainly)"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自confident（n.信心）"},{"type":"text","text":"['ka:nfrdantli]"},{"type":"entry","text":"multifaceted","headword":"multifaceted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 多方面的(having many facets or aspects)"},{"type":"text","text":"protean, various, versatile"},{"type":"text","text":"[mAlti'faesrtrd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"uncontroversial","headword":"uncontroversial"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj. 未引起争论的(not causing, or not likely to cause, any disagreement)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anka:ntra'vs:r]"},{"type":"entry","text":"noncontroversial","headword":"noncontroversial"},{"type":"entry","text":"enviable","headword":"enviable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.令人羡慕的(highly desirable)"},{"type":"text","text":"['enviabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自envy（n/v.美慕）"},{"type":"entry","text":"terrifying","headword":"terrifying"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 恐布的(causing terror or apprehension)"},{"type":"text","text":"['terrfarrn]"},{"type":"text","text":"frightening. intimidating, shocking"},{"type":"entry","text":"contention","headword":"contention"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 争论(the act of dispute; discord); 论:点(a statement one argues for as valid)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'ten{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：con（共同）+tent（拉）+ion→你拉我夺→争论"}]},{"number":193,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"prior","headword":"prior"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 在前的9(previous);优先的(taking precedence)"},{"type":"text","text":"['prarar]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：pri（看作prim，第一，首先）+or→在前的；优先的"},{"type":"text","text":"Students of the Great Crash of 1929 have never understood why even the"},{"type":"text","text":"most informed observers did not recognize and heed the prior economic danger"},{"type":"text","text":"signals that in retrospect seem so apparent."},{"type":"text","text":"antecedent, anterior, former, preceding"},{"type":"entry","text":"domain","headword":"domain"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 领±(territory, dominion);领域(field or sphere of activity or influence)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dau'mein]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：dom（控制）+ain→统治的地方→领土；领域"},{"type":"entry","text":"irrefutable","headword":"irrefutable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无可辩驳的，毋庸置疑的(impossible torefute)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'fju:tabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"inarguable, incontestable, incontrovertible"},{"type":"entry","text":"speculative","headword":"speculative"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 推理的，思索的(based on speculation);投机的(risky)"},{"type":"text","text":"['spekjalatrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"conjectured, guessed, supposed, surmised"},{"type":"entry","text":"affection","headword":"affection"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 喜爱(fond or tender feeling)"},{"type":"text","text":"ambitious"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'fek{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：affect（影响，感染）+ion→喜爱"},{"type":"text","text":"affective（adj感情的，表达感情的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"shortsighted","headword":"shortsighted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.缺乏远见的(lacking foresight)：近视的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Jo:rt'sartid]"},{"type":"text","text":"nearsighted"}]}]}